item.title: Software Developer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
We expect you to;
  • Have extensive knowledge of HTML5 and CSS3;
  • Have experience in JavaScript/JQuery;
  • Have experience in working with PHP;
  • Have experience in working with frameworks (Laravel);
  • Good knowledge of relational databases (MYSQL);
  • Have experience with WordPress/ Magento – would be a plus;
  • Be able to manage multiple tasks and prioritise work;
  • Have the ability to work collaboratively as part of a project team;
  • Have excellent English skills.
Your main responsibilities include;
  • Collaborate with business analysts and developers to produce software designs;
  • Transform software designs and specifications into high functioning code in the appropriate language;
  • Integrate individual software solutions to higher level systems;
  • Cooperate with web designers to match visual design intent;
  • Edit content and re-design web pages;
  • Test code periodically to ensure it produces the desirable results and perform debugging when necessary
  • Maintain and expand our websites;
  • Assist and support in the upkeeping of our websites.
  • Perform upgrades to make software and systems more secure and efficient.

item.title: Graphic Design Intern
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
Position is part of a formal internship program in professional development in the contract management services industry. Supports business units and assists in projects. Builds skills and knowledge in large corporate and team environment. The Graphic Artist is responsible for translating various brand designs into mechanical files and building precise and complete files, that are ready for email distribution or prepress/printing by utilizing a strong knowledge of layout, graphic design and print production. Required Education, Skills and Experience:
  • Prefer 4 completed semesters of graphic design
  • Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite and fluent in MS Office, Word, and PPT- Preferred
  • Experience in image manipulation and color correction
  • Ability to work within a fast-paced development cycle
  • Ability to apply and enforce style/brand guidelines
  • Detail oriented with excellent organizational/communication skills

item.title: Jr. Web Developer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
We stand for innovation and open standards. We stand for patients and the people who care for them. We stand for best practices and equal access to care. Together, we will create the experiences that define the future of care. Join Us!
As a Web Developer at Commure, you will:
  • Build easy-to-use and performant websites serving multiple partners across marketing and design.
  • Understand the technical constraints of a project, and make pragmatic tradeoffs with stakeholders.
  • Contribute to and maintain our interactive design system used across all digital properties.
  • Participate in the full development lifecycle, including estimation, design, development, testing, and deployment.
  • Collaborate with our marketing and design teams via regular design critiques and working sessions.
  • Review and respond to operational issues, escalating as necessary.
You have:
  • 3+ years of experience developing detailed websites.
  • Experience leading a project from start to finish.A strong portfolio URL.
  • Experience with standard web technology, including HTML, CSS, Javascript, TypeScript, and React.
  • You understand the importance of accessibility and performance, such as code minification and media optimization.
  • Previously worked with in-house design teams.
  • The ability to express ideas to both technical and non-technical individuals.
  • In-depth knowledge of design principles and best practices.
  • The ability to define and propose projects in addition to building them.
  • Excellent oral, written, and interpersonal communication skills.
  • Demonstrated critical-thinking, decision-making, and problem-solving skills.
  • The ability to operate on multiple projects simultaneously in a high-growth startup environment.A positive and proactive attitude.

item.title: Customer Support Specialist
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
Our Call Center Agents handle incoming orders, interact with third party providers, assist in solving guest concerns, and support the restaurant operations team. A Call Center Agent is the communication liaison of our team, making sure every customer has a great experience. If you are outgoing and friendly, efficient with computer entry, and have strong verbal communication skills, we look forward to speaking with you about joining our team! Requirements:
  • Provide excellent customer service experience for customers
  • Answer calls and input orders (customer/catering)
  • Provide information to callers regarding menus and services.
  • Support customer retention & recovery
  • Online brand reputation support (Respond to reviews, escalate issues, etc.)
  • Assist in delivery dispatch and tracking, for all restaurant locations
  • An evolving role, that may include responsibilities not listed above.

item.title: Junior Developer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
If you are extremely detail oriented, obsessed with delivering only the best service, love split testing and experimentation, have outstanding written and verbal communications skills, willing to learn more and implement new strategies, love to be a part of a team to change the future of admissions, and looking for a long-term mission with significant impact on society, then you need to apply. Now. What we offer:
  • Freedom to work from anywhere around the world. You never have to go to the "office".
  • Freedom to choose your hours. We focus on results not the hours or arbitrary 9 to 5.
  • Opportunity of stocks/shares in our fast growing company for exceptional team members that embody our core values.
  • Opportunity for growth, independent project development and career advancement.
  • Make a huge difference in the lives of aspiring future professionals and contribute to our outstanding success rate.
  • Be a part of our fast growing, innovative and leading academic consulting firm.
  • Be part of a team of A-players. We only hire the brightest individuals with the highest caliber, character and courage.
  • Comprehensive health, dental and disability insurance benefits.
  • Generous self-directed vacation policy for full-time team members.
  • $1,000 yearly personal and professional development fund.
  • Quarterly team dinners.
Roles and responsibilities:
  • Create and test new webpages on our websites with specific functionality and excellent attention to user interface.
  • Optimizing existing web pages on our website based on specific directions from our developer lead.
  • Development and testing of a new web application including the next generation of admissions screening softwares.
  • Maintaining Amazon AWS CentOs servers.
  • Maintaining and testing routine backups and restores.
  • Administering and configuring servers' Apache, PHP, and MySQL installations.
  • Monitoring and analyzing our systems and servers performance.
  • Provide technical support for incoming concerns and issues related to systems and software.
Requirements:
  • A Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering, or related fields. (Must have completed the degree)
  • Front and back-end knowledge and experience is an asset.
  • Expertise in programming with PHP, HTML5, JavaScript, CSS, MySQL, Laravel, CentOs and shell script are an asset.
  • 2 years of paid full-time job experience.

item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
Join us as a Customer Service Representative to answer questions, process transactions and assist customers by phone. You'll shine in this role if you have strong listening skills and enjoy a challenging, fast-paced environment. Work with us and you'll enjoy:
  • Full-Time Schedule (40 hours/week)
  • Starting Base Pay $12.00/hour
  • Pay Increase after 60 days to $13.50/hour
  • Pay Increase to $15.00/hour after 6 months in production
  • Performance bonus (Earn $1.00/hour + in addition to base pay)
  • Full benefits package including medical, dental, vision, life insurance and company matched 401(k)
  • 100% Paid Training
  • Tuition reimbursement program
Benefits:
  • 401(k) matching
  • Dental insurance
  • Health insurance
  • Life insurance
  • Tuition reimbursement
  • Vision insurance

item.title: UX/UI Web Designer & Developer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
Are you a seasoned UX/UI Web Designer & Developer with a diverse skill set? Do you enjoy blending strategy, creativity, and coding to create websites that generate high visitor to lead conversions? Is a supportive team environment that encourages ongoing skill development important to you? This position will work closely with our digital marketing teams to develop the strategy and execute the development for website projects to meet and exceed client goals. Core responsibilities include:
  • Develop custom, responsive WordPress themes according to design mockups
  • Apply UX and SEO conversion optimization into the strategy
  • Ability to work in various content management and proprietary systems
  • Install and manage appropriate plugins
  • Develop website forms and any other required functionality

item.title: Associate Software Engineer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
Are you interested in building products used by over millions people? Do you like shipping code at a rapid pace? lululemon is seeking Software Engineering intern who is passionate about building desktop web applications. Minimum Qualification:
  • Must be pursuing a degree in Software, Engineering, Computer science or related field.
  • Working Knowledge of Python, HTML/CSS/JS/React, or the ability to learn them quickly
  • Knowledge of software version control systems
  • Knowledge of how web applications works
  • Knowledge with unit testing frameworks.
  • A passion for solving problems and desire to understand how things work.
Our "must haves":
  • Proven work ethic with utmost integrity
  • Desire to excel and succeed
  • Self-awareness, with a desire for constant self improvement (goal -oriented)
  • Entrepreneurial spirit and an egoless nature
  • Self motivated, passionate, empathetic, approachable

  • 2+ years of customer service experience
  • Experience using multiple systems to identify solutions for the customer and the ability to manage multiple systems, tabs and issues at one time
  • Experience with follow up and closure for customer
  • Experience with thorough documentation of contact
  • Proven excelled customer service skills
  • Excellent verbal and written communications

  • Strong communication skills and multi-tasking skills

item.title: Web Developer/Designer
item.dc:creator: Egemenerd
item.content:encoded:
We are seeking an experienced, talented and passionate Web Developer/Designer with high level of usability experience, ideas and imagination to design intuitive web pages and web applications interfaces. This position requires a person with strong artistic abilities, creative approach to problem solving, usability knowledge, organizational skills, and great attention to detail. Specific Responsibilities:
  • Advanced knowledge of HTML, JavaScript/jQuery and CSS
  • jQuery UI Framework Design
  • Fluency in Photoshop and related designing tools; CSS Sprites
  • Knowledge of Web 2.0
  • Passion to innovate and design state of the art User Interfaces
  • Strong graphic designing skills and aesthetics
  • Support customers through email interaction with occasional phone calls to help troubleshoot more complex issues
Minimum Qualifications/Requirements:
  • Associates degree in related field preferred
  • Self-motivated and self managed with a high degree of analytical ability and intellectual curiosity
  • Experience delivering customer support using email and phone
  • Able to work effectively and efficiently with customers who have varying degrees of product and technical proficiency
